      "content": "i hear you, but he's literally just lying there saying he feels fine, just tired. if we call the ambulance he's gonna be so embarrassed and it'll just be a huge waste of time/money if it's just travel stress. isn't it common for people to have weird sensations after sitting on a plane for 12 hours? like maybe a pinched nerve or just low blood sugar from the flight? can we just give him some aspirin and some electrolytes and monitor him for a few hours to see if it passes?",
